{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T06:57:16.113Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Init Pitfalls"},{"type":"text","text":" (initialization pitfalls) are common mistakes in weight initialization that cause neural networks to fail training, converge slowly, or learn nothing at all. These errors are especially critical because they happen "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"before training starts"},{"type":"text","text":" and can make deep networks un-trainable from the first iteration."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The 4 Major Initialization Pitfalls"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pitfall 1: ❌ Zero Initialization"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"What"},{"type":"text","text":": Setting all weights to zero ("},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"W = 0"}},{"type":"text","text":")"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"What happens"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Every neuron outputs 0 in the forward pass\n- Gradients become 0 during backpropagation\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"No weight updates occur → no learning happens"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why it's catastrophic"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- All neurons receive "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"identical gradients"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- All weights update identically → "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"symmetry never breaks"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Network behaves like "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"a single neuron"},{"type":"text","text":" (linear model)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# BAD - Never do this\nW = np.zeros((100, 128))  # All zeros!"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Result"},{"type":"text","text":": Network is a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"linear model"},{"type":"text","text":" that can't capture non-linear relationships."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pitfall 2: ❌ Constant Non-Zero Initialization"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"What"},{"type":"text","text":": Setting all weights to the same constant (e.g., 0.5)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"What happens"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- All neurons start identical (same output)\n- Gradients are identical for all neurons\n- Updates happen identically → "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"neurons never diversify"},{"type":"text","text":".md)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why it's bad"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Same problem as zero initialization (symmetry)\n- Network becomes a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"single neuron"},{"type":"text","text":" despite having hundreds\n- Acts like a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"linear model"},{"type":"text","text":", can't learn non-linear patterns"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# BAD - Never do this\nW = np.ones((100, 128)) * 0.5  # All same value!"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Result"},{"type":"text","text":": Network fails to learn diverse features from data..md)"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pitfall 3: ❌ Very Small Random Values"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"What"},{"type":"text","text":": Random weights multiplied by a tiny factor (e.g., 0.01)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# BAD - Common mistake\nW = np.random.randn(100, 128) * 0.01  # Too small!"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"What happens"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Vanishing gradients"},{"type":"text","text":": Gradients become tiny → weights barely update\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Signal loss"},{"type":"text","text":": Activations diminish as they propagate through layers\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Slow convergence"},{"type":"text","text":": Network learns extremely slowly.md)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why it's bad"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- For deep networks: small weights × small weights ×... → exponentially small\n- Gradients shrink as they move backward → early layers train very slowly or not at all\n- Model doesn't reach optimum in training time"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Result"},{"type":"text","text":": Training takes forever or never reaches good performance."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pitfall 4: ❌ Very Large Random Values"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"What"},{"type":"text","text":": Random weights in large range (e.g., 0 to 1, or std=10)"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# BAD - Common mistake\nW = np.random.randn(100, 128) * 10  # Too large!"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"What happens"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Exploding gradients"},{"type":"text","text":": Gradients grow too large → unstable updates\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Saturation"},{"type":"text","text":": Activations saturate activation functions (sigmoid/tanh → gradient ≈ 0).md)\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"NaN values"},{"type":"text","text":": Weight swings cause overflow → "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"NaN"},{"type":"text","text":" (Not a Number)\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Divergence"},{"type":"text","text":": Loss oscillates wildly or diverges.md)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why it's bad"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Large weights × large weights ×... → exponentially large ("},{"type":"inlineMath","attrs":{"latex":"10^{6} \\cdot 10^{6} \\cdot 10^{6} = 10^{18}"}},{"type":"text","text":")\n- Can't reach optimum (requires small steps, not large swings)\n- Activation saturation → vanishing gradient despite large weights.md)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Result"},{"type":"text","text":": Training is unstable, loss diverges, or model crashes with NaN."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Summary Table: What Goes Wrong"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Pitfall"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Weight Range"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Primary Problem"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":